an for annual giving  alumni relations  reunion campaigns  regional programs and athletic development as well as coordinating the cultivation  solicitation and stewardship of more than 360 000 Rutgers alumni as well as other potential donors  He also served Rutgers as the executive director of the Scarlet R Club and associate athletic director for development  From 1984 to 1993  Crockett worked as a sales and marketing executive for Xerox and Digital Equipment Corporation  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 